                                                        Ready for MiFID II?
                                                    
MiFID II will take effect on January 3, 2018. This new framework is expected to transform Europe’s financial markets, with major implications for both buy-side and sell-side professionals. See how we can help you.




 



                                                        Unleashing American Energy
                                                    
IHS Markit Vice Chairman Daniel Yergin recently chaired panel discussions at the US Department of Energy, including a session on US energy policy that featured the Secretary of Energy, Secretary of the Interior, EPA Administrator and the Director of the National Economic Council. Learn more.




 



                                                        Working together to transform our world
                                                    
The IHS Markit 2016 Sustainability Report is now available. See how our colleagues, partners and customers are using business information in a holistic way to tackle economic, environmental and social challenges through a new global framework – the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals. Learn more.




 



                                                        Capturing the nation’s mood, hourly.
                                                    
Together with the Wall Street Journal, IHS Markit has launched the US Social Sentiment Index (USSI) – tracking millions of Twitter posts hourly to gauge the country’s attitudes by state and gender. The USSI offers organizations a near real-time lens into key market and consumer shifts. Read news release.




 



                                                        See the big picture and how it impacts you
                                                    
Improve efficiency, outpace competitors and drive growth with The New Intelligence from IHS Markit. We combine information, analytics and expertise in solutions that can help you see why things happen and focus on what matters. That’s why 50,000+ organizations, including 85% of the Fortune Global 500, rely on our perspective and insights.








 




