Get the latest intelligence on the components and systems that make up a vehicle

SupplierInsight’s landing page is the gateway to IHS Automotive component and technology research, thought leadership and analysis. The home page enables you to access all services, view featured stories, scroll through a feed of the most recently added assets, and navigate assets by category/topic.With access to the latest news on events and trends to deep-dive topical reports, SupplierInsight provides you with unparalleled insight into vehicle components and systems. Service content includes:






Sector news and analysis
Topical reports
Supplier profiles
Who Supplies Whom survey database
Access to analysts and monthly webinars
Model-level forecasts, technology fitment and supplier relationships (optional add-on)







SupplierInsight Services

SupplierInsight offers a lens into more than a dozen vehicle component categories. Each service provides the insight you need to anticipate future demand, access competitive intelligence and stay abreast of changing dynamics.


Autonomous Driving ServiceAnalyzes the shift towards increased automation of driver controls and its impact on mobility as well as the value chain mapping of autonomous driving. Topics covered include:ADAS sensors: Radar, camera, lidarApplications: Adaptive cruise control, blind spot, lane keep assist, park assist and similarVehicle-to-vehicle communicationsAutonomous drivingNew mobilityChassis ServiceFocuses on braking, steering, noise/vibration/harshness, and suspension control as well as increasing electrification of chassis systems. Topics covered include:Brake actuation systems and supply chainBrake friction materialsDamper systems and actuationSteering systemTire technologyE-Mobility ServiceCenters on the enablers of e-mobility such as infrastructure and the related component technology. Topics covered include:Electric vehicle/hybrid vehicle/plug-in vehicle electric vehicle/fuel-cell electric vehicle production volumesLegislation and incentivesElectric vehicle charging infrastructure and wireless powerRegional e-mobility profilesElectric vehicle technologies: Battery, motors, DC/DC converters, invertersVehicle specifications and supplier dataHydrogen fuel-cell electric vehiclesLearn moreElectrics and ElectronicsFocuses on board electrical networks, power electronics and control electronics and architectures applied to comfort functions and other in-vehicle functions. Topics covered include:Electronics applied to comfort functionsIn-vehicle electrical architecture (e.g., 48 volt systems for hybrid and non-hybrid applications)Model-level forecasts on central body control modules, immobilizers, keyless entry, power sunroofs, power windows, tire pressure monitoring, wiring harnessesInfotainmentCentered on technology, OEM strategy and supply base assessment of headunit system, in-car connectivity and telematics. Topics covered include:Infotainment technologies: Head unit systems, telematics, acousticsSpecifications: Head unit type, projection capable plus type, operating system, storage technology type, number of speakers, wattage, active noise cancellation, connection type, connection bandwidth, Wi-FiTopics: Premium audio, connectivity, business models, navigation and display audio, in-vehicle wireless device chargingInterior Comfort and Passive Safety ServiceProvides insight, context, data, and analytics for the key systems that make up a vehicle’s interior and for how materials and functionality are changing to meet consumer demand and emission compliance. Topics covered include:Passive safety systems and subsystems (e.g., airbag modules)Decorative and interior finish (e.g., door-trim panels, seat materials)Cockpit and seat-comfort functionsLighting ServiceProvides insight, context, data, and analytics for the key technologies that are core to the developments in the lighting sector. Topics covered include:Front lights, front light electronic control module (ECU), tail lampsECU fitment and type, low beam type, high beam type, bulb count, power consumption, adaptive function and type, camera fitment and lighting functionMaterials and Lightweighting ServiceAnalyses material change opportunities, mostly to sustain light weighting or sustainability efforts. Topics covered include:Weight reduction and joining techniquesMaterial changes (e.g., plastics, carbon fiber, aluminum, alloys)RecyclabilityPowertrain Components and TechnologiesTracks developments of existing or new component technologies applied to engine and transmission as well as fuel efficiency and emission regulations. Topics covered include:Valvetrain, intake and injection technologiesExhaust and emission control technologiesMain engine structural componentsDrivetrain architectures and technologiesServices, Apps and SoftwareProvides concise evaluations and forecasts of infotainment OS platforms, apps integration via smartphones and infotainment systems, apps categories and the latest developments of relevant players. Topics covered include:Infotainment OS trends (GENIVI, Android, Linux, QNX, Microsoft)Apple CarPlay, Android Auto, MirrorLink, SmartDeviceLink, Baidu CarlifeMobile apps (e.g., Pandora, Facebook, etc.)Telematics services (eCall/bCall)Usage-based insuranceOver-the-air updatesCyber securityThermal ManagementDeep dives on components enabling thermal and air cabin comfort as well as management of heat dissipation in other critical component areas (for example Cooled EGR). Topics covered include:Heating, Ventilating and Air Conditioning (HVAC) systems technology and its managementThermal management systems applied to powertrain components (e.g., cooled exhaust gas recirculation)Model-level forecasts: AC-compressor, condenser/dryer, hose/tube; charge air cooler; cooled exhaust gas recirculation; engine cooling (plus active grill shutter); HVAC-blower, control panel, module, electronic control module, thermostatic expansion valuve, intelligent engine coolingUser Interface and ExperienceAnalyzes how displays, speech recognition and other interfaces are revolutionizing the way users interact with vehicles. Topics covered include:Display systems: Instrument cluster display, center stack display, head-up displayOther HMI outputs: Haptics, augmented reality, emerging display applicationsHMI inputs: Speech, touch screens, touchpads, controllers, hard keys, gesture and proximityUsability insights: Late-model vehicles evaluated for infotainment system usabilityTopics: Automotive user interfaces, HMI trends, usability reviews, emerging display applicationsOEM Strategy ServiceMonitors OEM sourcing strategies as well as developments in the supplier sector on a regional basis. Topics covered include:OEM platform strategyOEM production strategyOEM sourcing strategyLocal supply base availability







 






