Open Registration Intelligence Training Schedule 2017                    

OSINT Methods & Techniques (2 days)Social Media Intelligence (1.5 days)
Discover the latest methods and techniques to improve the way you gather, process and report open-source information and intelligenceLearn how to more efficiently and effectively exploit social media sources to inform multi-source intelligence assessments.11-12 July, Singapore: Fully booked13-14 July, Singapore: Register now3-4 October, London: Register now5-6 October, London: Register now27-28 November, London: Register now29-30 November, London: Register now







Customized Training Solutions 

To discuss customized training requirements, please contact us: Janes




Workshops

We offer customized training workshops that fit specific client requirements. They are particularly useful for organizations that have large OSINT analyst teams. The workshops can be delivered either on-site or hosted by us and can combine elements from pre-defined courses or newly created courses.Customized Training: Specialized CoursesCyber-Security for OSINT Analysts: Practical measures for OSINT analysts to stay safe from potential cyber-threats while gathering information onlineStrategic Futures Analysis: Understanding the future and producing estimative intelligence using techniques such as scenario analysisIslamist Extremist Media Analysis: Monitoring and interpreting discourse by extremists and supportersIntroduction to Geospatial Intelligence: Use of OSINT to generate geospatial intelligence/interpretation of OSINT-based GEOINT productsOSINT for Investigators: Specialized OSINT methods, techniques, and tools to support targeted investigationsOSINT for Defence Industry: Effective use of OSINT in defense industry analysis and competitive intelligence, including analyzing national defense offset programs
Process

Needs analysis: IHS Markit OSINT experts have an initial discussion with you to understand your existing OSINT practices and to identify how our training will benefit youTraining delivery: We deliver the content at an agreed upon schedule that is flexible in terms of participant numbers and training timeAdditional training: We offer additional courses to meet your specific needs, focusing on specialist skills and knowledgeReview: We conduct a post-training review to discuss benefits and challenges arising from the training
Principles

Relevant: We deliver knowledge and skills that trainees can immediately apply in their daily operations when they return to workPractical: We try to avoid a ‘chalk-and-talk’ approach, emphasizing learning through hands-on guided exercises. We choose individual and group tasks that relate to the common intelligence problems faced by traineesCutting-Edge: All course instructors are experienced OSINT professionals who are not simply trainers, but are currently engaged in delivering OSINT reports and briefings to our clients, ensuring their expertise is state of the artInspirational: We encourage a relaxed and collaborative atmosphere in our training sessions, where trainees can feel free to ask questions, share knowledge and expertise, challenge their tutors and emerge inspired to continue the process of learning and professional development






Open Registration Training Solutions

To discuss customized training requirements, please contact us: Janes




OSINT Methods and Techniques

Discover the latest methods and techniques to improve the way you gather, process and report open-source information and intelligence. As a trainee, you will:Develop knowledge and skills necessary to analyze and deconstruct intelligence tasks, frame research requirements and focus collection activitiesLearn methods to collect, collate, and process open-source informationLearn how to conduct source and content analysis, helping to challenge assumptions and create more rigorous reportsLearn how to communicate open-source intelligence assessments clearlyUnderstand how to conduct safe and optimized searching of online sources
Social Media Intelligence (SOCMINT) Methods and Techniques

Learn how to more efficiently and effectively exploit social media sources to inform multi-source intelligence assessments. As a trainee, you will:Understand the social media landscape, including popular social media platforms, current trends, opportunities and threatsUnderstand social media's uses and limitations and how it can be used as a component of a broader, open-source intelligence programUnderstand how SOCMINT can be employed in a range of intelligence activities from the strategic to the operationalDevelop greater social media fluency by acquiring skills to more efficiently and effectively monitor social media and incorporate insights into a multi-source intelligence product
Principles

Relevant: We deliver knowledge and skills that trainees can immediately apply in their daily operations when they return to workPractical: We try to avoid a ‘chalk-and-talk’ approach, emphasizing learning through hands-on guided exercises. We choose individual and group tasks that relate to the common intelligence problems faced by traineesCutting-Edge: All course instructors are experienced OSINT professionals who are not simply trainers, but are currently engaged in delivering OSINT reports and briefings to our clients, ensuring their expertise is state of the artInspirational: We encourage a relaxed and collaborative atmosphere in our training sessions, where trainees can feel free to ask questions, share knowledge and expertise, challenge their tutors and emerge inspired to continue the process of learning and professional development
Pricing

Prices include all relevant course materials, handouts and copies of the presentations, which will be provided on a USB memory stick at the end of the course.OSINT Methods & Techniques (per person):Corporate Rate: $1,900Government Rate: $1,600(Discounts available for group bookings)Social Media Intelligence (per person)Corporate rate: $1,425Government/Military rate: $1,200Both coursesCorporate rate: $3,325Government/Military rate: $2,800Please read the IHS OSINT Training Cancellation, Postponement and Substitutions Policy. (PDF, 39 KB)
